# Copy to the repo root as `.env` (Docker Compose loads it automatically):
#   cp .env.integration.example .env
# Full checklist: docs/INTEGRATION_STARTUP.md
# Then rebuild so Next.js embeds NEXT_PUBLIC_* correctly:
#   docker compose -f docker-compose.integration.yml up -d --build
#
# Replace the host with your public IP/DNS (e.g. sslip.io). Open security groups for 3000 and 8000.
#
# EC2: ``scripts/deploy-ec2.sh`` derives NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL from DEVNEST_FRONTEND_PUBLIC_BASE_URL
# when NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL is unset (fixes browsers still calling localhost:8000).
#
# --- Database (integration / EC2) ---
# One knob for RDS: set ``DEVNEST_COMPOSE_DATABASE_URL`` to your ``postgresql+psycopg://...`` DSN (Compose
# copies it into both ``DATABASE_URL`` and ``DEVNEST_DATABASE_URL`` in the backend container). For bundled
# Postgres, omit all three (``DEVNEST_COMPOSE_DATABASE_URL``, ``DATABASE_URL``, and RDS in ``backend/.env``).
# App + Alembic resolve the same URL via ``get_settings().database_url`` (``DEVNEST_DATABASE_URL`` wins over
# ``DATABASE_URL`` if they ever differ).

DEVNEST_FRONTEND_PUBLIC_BASE_URL=http://98-92-163-201.sslip.io:3000
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=http://98-92-163-201.sslip.io:8000
#
# Optional short-lived auth/RDS debugging (no secrets in responses):
#   DEVNEST_AUTH_DIAGNOSTICS=true  → backend GET /internal/devnest-auth-diagnostics
#   Same on the frontend service → GET /api/internal/devnest-diagnostics (Next→FastAPI probe).
# DEVNEST_AUTH_DIAGNOSTICS=
#
# --- Optional fail-fast (backend + workspace-worker; default false in compose) ---
# DEVNEST_EXPECT_EXTERNAL_POSTGRES=true  → abort if DB host resolves to bundled service name ``postgres``
# DEVNEST_EXPECT_REMOTE_GATEWAY_CLIENTS=true  → abort if DEVNEST_BASE_DOMAIN is app.lvh.me / app.devnest.local
# ``scripts/deploy-ec2.sh`` sets both when DATABASE_URL is set for RDS deploys.
# DEVNEST_EXPECT_EXTERNAL_POSTGRES=
# DEVNEST_EXPECT_REMOTE_GATEWAY_CLIENTS=
